e create, add, and remove. It looks like I need to catch issues early while testing, so I'll include event multicast tests in a dedicated file. It’s essential to also check for generated classes to avoid problems with the initial call.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting user code**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the need to inspect the user code filter. I want to ensure that the tests are only allowed for certain packages. It’s essential to verify that everything works within the expected parameters and doesn’t break any rules. This could help maintain security and efficiency. So, I'll focus on checking which packages are allowed and how the filtering operates to ensure smooth testing without any hiccups.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_l74l9UupN7RUftGWmVihrZZD|fc_054e1f0eaf8484c20169f5b7db20d081918e8cfa2de994d6fb", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/user-code-filter.json"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1558, "output": 774, "cacheRead": 31232, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33564, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777711053689, "responseId": "resp_054e1f0eaf8484c20169f5b7ce21dc8191a330211dfb8c2bc1"}}
